  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-10-30",
    "date": "2019-11-13T15:25:17Z",
    "text": "Prevent Family Fire Act of 2019\n\nThis bill allows a new business-related tax credit for 10% of the amount of\u00a0the first retail sale of a safe firearm storage device. The amount upon which the credit is based may not exceed $400.\n\nA \"safe firearm storage device\" is a device that (1) is designed and marketed to deny unauthorized access to, or rendering inoperable, a firearm or ammunition; and (2) is secured by a combination lock, key lock, or lock based on biometric information.\n\nThis credit terminates after December 31, 2026."
  },
